        "<a href=\"https://colab.research.google.com/github/crowell97/ES2245/blob/main/es2245_lecture25.ipynb\" target=\"_parent\"><img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" alt=\"Open In Colab\"/></a>"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Lecture 25: Spatial Datasets\n",
        "\n",
        "**Course:** EARTHSC 2245 - Introductory Data Analysis for Earth and Environmental Sciences\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook explores various ways to download geospatial data and manipulate it\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YGECdqJQuhtM"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Global Temperatures\n",
        "1: We are going to use MERRA-2 (Modern-Era Retrospective analysis for Research and Applications). Instead of a camera on a satellite taking individual snapshots, MERRA-2 is a continuous, mathematically modeled grid of the entire planet that incorporates satellite data."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rATQmYBM2rPh"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Install the necessary libraries\n",
        "#!pip install earthaccess xarray netCDF4 h5netcdf cartopy matplotlib"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ux-lO_rz0pyh"
      },
      "execution_count": 81,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import earthaccess\n",
        "import xarray as xr\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import cartopy.crs as ccrs\n",
        "import cartopy.feature as cfeature\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set plotting style\n",
        "plt.style.use('ggplot')\n",
        "%matplotlib inline"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F7Cp1Q2S0qd8"
      },
      "execution_count": 82,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Authentication\n",
        "\n",
        "You will need a NASA Earthdata login to perform this notebook. In addition, you will need to authorize specific applications. For this one, its NASA GESDISC DATA ARCHIVE that you will need to add."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dmw1RiZ_2yiC"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Authenticate with NASA Earthdata\n",
        "auth = earthaccess.login(strategy=\"interactive\")\n",
        "\n",
        "if auth.authenticated:\n",
        "    print(\"Successfully authenticated with NASA Earthdata.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Authentication failed.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "NbzxYEdP0taV",
        "outputId": "146a9815-56bb-43c4-ee1a-6077611ceddc"
      },
      "execution_count": 83,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Successfully authenticated with NASA Earthdata.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Search for Global Data\n",
        "\n",
        "We are searching for the M2T1NXSLV product. This contains 2-dimensional, hourly, single-level atmospheric diagnostics (including 2-meter air temperature)."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NgCeHXn33rXG"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Search for just one day of data.\n",
        "# In MERRA-2, 1 granule contains 24 hourly global snapshots for that specific day.\n",
        "results = earthaccess.search_data(\n",
        "    short_name='M2T1NXSLV',\n",
        "    temporal=(\"2025-01-01\", \"2025-01-01\"),\n",
        "    count=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Found {len(results)} global granule.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "1mRz6VvI0vX1",
        "outputId": "4188b203-0e29-45e2-f846-bd73faf0b3f1"
      },
      "execution_count": 84,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Found 1 global granule.\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/earthaccess/results.py:343: FutureWarning: As of version 1.0, `DataGranule.size` will be accessed as an attribute; e.g. use `DataCollection.size` **not** `DataCollection.size()`\n",
            "  self[\"size\"] = self.size()\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Cloud-Native Loading\n",
        "We use earthaccess.open() to stream the file, and pass it directly to xarray."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kA9U5azI33rO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Download the file locally (This handles all the complex authentication perfectly)\n",
        "print(\"Downloading MERRA-2 data...\")\n",
        "downloaded_files = earthaccess.download(results, local_path=\".\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Open the newly downloaded local file\n",
        "# earthaccess.download returns a list of file paths (e.g., ['./MERRA2_400.tavg...nc4'])\n",
        "ds = xr.open_dataset(downloaded_files[0], engine='h5netcdf')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nDataset loaded successfully! Available variables include:\")\n",
        "print(list(ds.data_vars.keys())[:10])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 235,
