          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Data Extraction and Math\n",
        "The dataset contains a variable called T2M (2-meter air temperature). It has three dimensions: Time (24 hours), Latitude, and Longitude. We will isolate a single hour and convert the units."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T7WcQSV83_pQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Extract the temperature variable\n",
        "temp_kelvin = ds['T2M']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Isolate the 12th hour of the day (Noon UTC) using .isel() (index selection)\n",
        "temp_kelvin_noon = temp_kelvin.isel(time=12)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert from Kelvin to Celsius\n",
        "temp_celsius = temp_kelvin_noon - 273.15\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Global Temp Range: {float(temp_celsius.min()):.1f}°C to {float(temp_celsius.max()):.1f}°C\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "zffl-3Rl0zq2",
        "outputId": "ad583405-2491-416a-9803-8a1526932d02"
      },
      "execution_count": 86,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Global Temp Range: -55.0°C to 42.2°C\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Publication-Quality Mapping\n",
        "Because this data covers the whole globe, standard plots look distorted at the poles. We will use Cartopy to wrap our data onto a Robinson projection (a classic map shape)."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "x1MCNbm94FMf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Setup a Cartopy Figure with a Robinson Projection\n",
        "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))\n",
        "ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1, projection=ccrs.Robinson())\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Add geographic features for context\n",
        "ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE, linewidth=0.8, edgecolor='black')\n",
        "ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linewidth=0.4, linestyle=':', edgecolor='black')\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Plot the data\n",
        "# CRITICAL: We must use transform=ccrs.PlateCarree() to tell Cartopy\n",
        "# that our raw data is in standard Latitude/Longitude coordinates.\n",
        "plot = temp_celsius.plot(\n",
        "    ax=ax,\n",
        "    transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),\n",
        "    cmap='coolwarm',       # Blue for cold, Red for hot\n",
        "    vmin=-40, vmax=40,     # Lock the color scale from -40C to 40C\n",
        "    cbar_kwargs={\n",
        "        'label': 'Temperature (°C)',\n",
        "        'shrink': 0.7,\n",
        "        'orientation': 'horizontal',\n",
        "        'pad': 0.05\n",
        "    }\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Final touches\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Global 2-Meter Air Temperature at Noon UTC\\nNASA MERRA-2 Assimilation Data\", fontsize=16, pad=10)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 633
        },
        "id": "k4k3tAVA01cv",
        "outputId": "9139c6e5-5788-45cb-84c9-1358dac03562"
      },
      "execution_count": 87,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1400x700 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
