      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##2: Mapping Ocean Currents with High-Resolution Sea Surface Temp\n",
        "\n",
        "For this section, we are going to use a Level 4 (L4) dataset. In NASA terminology, Level 4 means the data has been mathematically gridded and gap-filled.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "We will map the Gulf Stream using the MUR SST (Multi-scale Ultra-high Resolution Sea Surface Temperature) dataset. It provides a stunning, high-definition look at ocean currents, and it works perfectly right out of the box.\n",
        "\n",
        "We will use standard scientific libraries. cartopy handles the map projections, and xarray handles the multi-dimensional NetCDF data."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gWTukA5d81X1"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#!pip install earthaccess xarray netCDF4 cartopy matplotlib"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hZ_kdDkj88Nr"
      },
      "execution_count": 88,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import earthaccess\n",
        "import xarray as xr\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import cartopy.crs as ccrs\n",
        "import cartopy.feature as cfeature\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set a dark background style to make the ocean temperatures pop\n",
        "plt.style.use('dark_background')\n",
        "%matplotlib inline"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EPk8WyOD9AHz"
      },
      "execution_count": 89,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Authentication\n",
        "Because we are pulling from PO.DAAC, this standard login is all you need."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BGZzCLZB-KJE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "auth = earthaccess.login(strategy=\"interactive\")\n",
        "\n",
        "if auth.authenticated:\n",
        "    print(\"Successfully authenticated with NASA Earthdata.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Authentication failed. Please check credentials.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "LBRwcfI69DN1",
        "outputId": "bcd527c9-37f4-4b07-9e53-5c39c1e75aab"
      },
      "execution_count": 90,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Successfully authenticated with NASA Earthdata.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Data Discovery\n",
        "We are searching for MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1. This is a daily, global dataset with an incredible 1km resolution. We will grab just a single day's file."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "P7fPMAcg-OE6"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Search for MUR SST for a specific day in the summer\n",
        "results = earthaccess.search_data(\n",
        "    short_name='MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1',\n",
        "    temporal=(\"2025-08-01\", \"2025-08-01\"),\n",
        "    count=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Found {len(results)} global dataset.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "3TTNKE7A9F1F",
        "outputId": "e4a2f55e-ff28-49c9-a8be-18f0a12b3abb"
      },
      "execution_count": 91,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Found 1 global dataset.\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/earthaccess/results.py:343: FutureWarning: As of version 1.0, `DataGranule.size` will be accessed as an attribute; e.g. use `DataCollection.size` **not** `DataCollection.size()`\n",
            "  self[\"size\"] = self.size()\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Download and Load\n",
        "Because this is a 1km global dataset, the file is about 400MB. We will download it locally to ensure a perfectly stable connection, then open it with xarray."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Rtmah5M7-Wfj"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "print(\"Downloading high-resolution SST data (approx 400MB)...\")\n",
        "downloaded_files = earthaccess.download(results, local_path=\".\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Open the downloaded file\n",
        "ds = xr.open_dataset(downloaded_files[0])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nDataset successfully loaded! Variables:\")\n",
        "print(list(ds.data_vars.keys()))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 235,
          "referenced_widgets": [
            "d7f6a81bb3ed4ddda26dec5244f23505",
