    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "###3: Tracking the 2025 Kamchatka Tsunami with SWOT Satellite Altimetry\n",
        "\n",
        "Because SWOT uses a wide-swath radar altimeter (the KaRIn instrument), it provides unprecedented 2D maps of Sea Surface Height Anomalies (SSHA), making it uniquely capable of capturing the fine-scale wave dispersion of a tsunami as it propagates across the Pacific.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "v85kN6lZ-_-R"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Install the necessary geospatial and data retrieval libraries\n",
        "#!pip install earthaccess xarray h5netcdf cartopy matplotlib numpy"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "j7Vdolrk_CMH"
      },
      "execution_count": 96,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import earthaccess\n",
        "import xarray as xr\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import cartopy.crs as ccrs\n",
        "import cartopy.feature as cfeature\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set a dark background style to make the wave anomalies pop\n",
        "plt.style.use('dark_background')\n",
        "%matplotlib inline"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1sX-vt2G_En3"
      },
      "execution_count": 97,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Authenticate with NASA Earthdata\n",
        "auth = earthaccess.login(strategy=\"interactive\")\n",
        "\n",
        "if auth.authenticated:\n",
        "    print(\"Successfully authenticated with NASA Earthdata.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Authentication failed. Please check your credentials.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "F3u1c0MD_G9w",
        "outputId": "7aa8394a-05e6-43c3-94a0-30913af616a1"
      },
      "execution_count": 98,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
